        </statement>
        <solution permid="cWJ">
          <p permid="TRs">
          The coefficients must be either 0 or 1.  The coefficient of <m>x^2</m> must be 1, otherwise the degree would be less than 2.  For each of the other terms, we could have coefficient 0 or 1, so there are 4 polynomials:<m>x^2 + x + 1</m>,            <m>x^2 + x</m>,            <m>x^2 + 1</m>, and <m>x^2</m>. 
