          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution permid="ofI">
          <p permid="tdW">
          For the sum, it is easiest to think of <m>z = a+bi</m>, since now <m>a+bi+a-bi = 2a</m>.  For the product, write the number in polar form: <m>z = re^{i\theta}</m> so <m>\bar z = re^{-i\theta}</m>.  Thus <m>z\cdot\bar z = re^{i\theta}re^{-i\theta} = r^2e^{0} = r^2</m>.
